Systemd is a software suite that provides an array of system components for Linux operating systems.
It manages (on / off / reboot ...). It also manages the system always (system) work in particular: set the hostname, configure the loopback interface, 
set up and mount the filesystem as / sys / proc ...
It is traditional & mother of init system which is the first process get started by kernel and holding PID 1.

SysVinit is the first process that is executed once the Linux kernel loads.

Upstart is an event-based replacement for the /sbin/init daemon which handles starting of tasks and services during boot, 
stopping them during shutdown and supervising them while the system is running.
